                <p class="text-justify">Do Alaska Airlines allow you to travel with pets? Yes, passengers at Alaska Airlines can definitely travel with their pets. However, they must follow some of Alaska Airlines' pet policy guidelines. If you want to make bookings with your pet, dial Alaska Airlines at +1-800-252-7522 or +1 888-370-4802 to contact CRO, who will help you with the bookings. Ready to go on a weekend trip with your furry friend? Quickly plan your trip with Alaska Airlines and travel with your buddy to your desired destination. While booking a flight with your pet through Alaska Airlines, you must go through the Alaska Airlines Pet policy. This is to make sure you have a stress-free and seamless travel experience. You can only bring dogs, cats, rabbits, and household birds in the main cabin when traveling with Alaska Airlines. </p>

                <p class="text-justify">Passengers booking an adjacent seat can carry a maximum of two pet carriers in the main cabin. Passengers are not allowed to book seats for themselves in an exit row or bulkhead row. As per the Alaska Airlines pet policy, your pet falls under your carry-on allotment. Simply put, you can only bring a pet with a personal item or standard carry-on bag. You are not allowed to carry both. The Alaska Airlines dog and cat policies state that your dog and cat must be at least eight weeks old. The flights come with an Alaska Airlines pet fee. They must be vaccinated. Also, you must carry a health certificate from a veterinarian. When it comes to travelers, they must be 18 years or older. If they are more than 18, then only they can fly with a dog or a cat in the cabin. The pets must fit in the carrier, including the head and tail. One must ensure it easily turns around, stands, and lies in its original position. In the First class, only three pets are allowed. In the main cabin, only eight can be accommodated (three and eight per carrier per flight). </p>


                <h2>How to Book a Flight with Pet on Alaska Airlines? </h2>

                <p class="text-justify">Follow the steps to book an Alaska Airlines pet policy cabin: </p>

                <ul>
                    <li>If you are flying with your pet and want to book an Alaska Airlines flight, then make sure to visit www.alaskaair.com  or dial +1-800-252-7522 or +1 888-370-4802. </li>
                    <li>Over there, make sure to choose your trip type. Enter your travel details in the given fields. </li>
                    <li>Select your departure and arrival date and destinations besides the other details. Once done, click on “Find Flights. </li>
                    <li>Get ready to choose the flight from the search results. Click “Add to cart.” </li>
                    <li>Head to check the price summary and make your bookings. </li>
                    <li>Fill in your details. Once done, click on “Request Special Assistance. ”There, you need to select “Service Animal” and click “Continue.” </li>
                    <li>In the empty fields, enter the contact details and click "Continue."You can select your seat according to your preference. </li>
                    <li>The last step is to check the fare summary, after which you need to make the payment for your bookings by following the steps mentioned. </li>
                </ul>


