                <h3>Things to Know about Alaska Pet Travel Requirements</h3>


                <ul>
                    <li>You can't transfer pets in the baggage compartment to other carriers in Alaska airlines. Pets in this airline always are claimed and rechecked to the connecting airline. </li>


                    <li>The Pet travel fee in the <a href="https://www.faresmatch.com/alaska-airlines-flights-reservations.aspx"><b>Alaska Airlines Reservations</b></a> for the passengers is $100 for One Way travel. </li>

                    <li>For the travel of Hawaii, only cats and dogs are accepted according to the Alaska Airlines Pet Policy. Hawaii has a unique identity, and it is a rabies-free state. </li>

                    <li>A passenger who wants to travel in Alaska with a pet must be 18 years old with a pet in the cabin. If you are going with your pet in Alaska's cabin, you will also not get a seat behind the emergency exit row seat, bulkhead, or any seat with an airbag safety belt. </li>


                    <li>In the First Class Cabin of Alaska Airlines Flights, only one pet carrier is allowed per flight. </li>

                    <li>In the main cabin of Alaska Airlines, only five pet carriers per flight are allowed. </li>
                </ul>


